In this article, President Barack Obama sends a letter to the Speaker of the House, requesting that Congress consider budget amendments for various departments and agencies. The amendments will increase the overall discretionary budget authority by $155 million in the Fiscal Year 2011 Budget. The President believes these amendments are necessary to accurately reflect the policies assumed in the budget. The specific details of the amendments can be found in the letter from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, which is enclosed with the letter.